-- 
Maryland, Virginia Advance to 2011 Men’s Lacrosse Championship Final

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-05-29T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-29/maryland-virginia-advance-to-men-s-lacrosse-championship-final.html
The  University of Maryland  and the
 University of Virginia  advanced to the college men’s lacrosse
Tournament final.  Maryland defeated defending champion Duke University 9-4
to reach tomorrow’s National College Athletic Association
lacrosse finals for the first time since 1998. Virginia beat
the University of Denver 14-8 for its ninth chance at the title
at M&T Bank Stadium in Baltimore.  Grant Catalino had three goals and Joe Cummings added two
yesterday for Maryland, which last won the tournament in 1975
when the Terrapins defeated Navy. Goalie Nick Amato had 13
saves.  Blue Devils goalie Dan Wigrizer had nine saves.  In the other semifinal, Virginia, which led 9-2 at halftime,
got three goals apiece from Steele Stanwick, Chris Bocklet and
Mark Cockerton. Goalie Adam Ghitelman had 10 saves for the
Cavaliers.  Jeremy Noble led the scoring for the Pioneers with three
goals. Jamie Faus recorded eight saves.  Virginia last won the title in 2006 when the Cavaliers
beat  Massachusetts .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  